					<h3>It’s Shark Week in Monterey Bay</h3>
					<img src="/images/166.jpg" alt="Sharks while Whale Watching in Monterey Bay California with Stagnaro Charters">
					<p>Catching up on recent sightings from this week: MONDAY 6/29: 8 humpback whales, with several close drive-bys, flukes. 15 Risso’s Dolphin, close good looks  with mother/calf pairs. TUESDAY 6/30: 2 humpbacks, tail throws, peck slapping, and 4 white sharks–one was 10 feet long, right under the boat for two minutes. Wednesday – Friday we checked out more <a href="http://www.ksbw.com/news/great-white-sharks-still-swimming-at-aptos-capitola-beaches/33881234?utm_campaign=KSBW+TV+Action+News+8&utm_medium=FBPAGE" title="Sharks near Santa Cruz, CA" target="_blank">sharks near Santa Cruz</a>, and we continue to see humpback whales feeding and showing beautiful surface behaviors! We had a particularly friendly animal at the bow of the boat on Thursday, what a majestic sight! Join us this summer!</p>
